House Resolution 124
By: Representatives Scott of the 76th, Schofield of the 63rd, and Davis of the 87th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the National Council of Negro Women; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the National Council of Negro Women (NCNW) was founded in 1935 by Dr.
4 Mary McLeod Bethune, an influential educator and activist, and for more than 50 years, the
5 iconic Dr. Dorothy Irene Height served as national president; and
6 WHEREAS, NCNW is an "organization of organizations" composed of 330 campus and
7 community-based sections as well as 38 national women's organizations, enlightening,
8 inspiring, and connecting more than two million women and men; and
9 WHEREAS, NCNW programs are grounded on a foundation of critical concerns known as
10 "NCNW Priorities," which include advocating for education; encouraging entrepreneurship,
11 financial literacy, and economic stability; informing women about health; promoting
12 healthcare access; upholding civic engagement; and campaigning for sound public policy and
13 social justice; and
14 WHEREAS, the State Coalition of Georgia for NCNW was established on August 20, 2016,
15 through the efforts of Dr. A. Lois Keith, with Shara Denton of Valdosta, Georgia, elected as
