16 the first state president to bolster NCNW's mission of leading, empowering, and advocating
17 for African American women, their families, and their communities; and
18 WHEREAS, the State Coalition of Georgia for NCNW is now led by Dr. Darlene
19 Ruffin-Alexander, convening over 13 community sections and 16 collegiate sections
20 throughout the state and hosting the annual NCNW Day at the Capitol as well as biennial
21 Leadership Training, State Conferences, and Bethune/Height Recognition Programs; and
22 WHEREAS, the State Coalition of Georgia is dedicated to sustaining the Core-4 priorities
23 of NCNW, which include Economic Empowerment and Entrepreneurship, Education
24 Empowerment and STEAM, Health Equity, and Social Justice.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
26 the members of this body recognize and commend the National Council of Negro Women
27 for its many outstanding contributions on behalf of women in this state and beyond as well
28 as extend best wishes for continued success.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
30 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
31 National Council of Negro Women.
